This paper focuses on understanding search behaviour in the context of mobile devices, which is closely related to information retrieval (cs.IR) and human-computer interaction (cs.HC). The study also involves analyzing the collected data, which could fall under computational linguistics (cs.CL) or cyber security (cs.CYBER) depending on the specific methods used. Finally, the study involves understanding the impact of context on search behaviour, which could fall under social and information networks (cs.SI).
